'''Burlesque metaphor''' is an amusing, overstated or grotesque comparison or [[examplification]].<ref name="HoggBlake2001">{{cite book|author1=Richard Milne Hogg|author2=N. Norman Francis Blake|author3=John Algeo |author4=Roger Lass |author5=Robert W. Burchfield|title=The Cambridge History of the English Language|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=ia5tHVtQPn8C&pg=PA613|accessdate=24 May 2013|date=7 February 2001|publisher=Cambridge University Press|isbn=978-0-521-26479-2|page=613–}}</ref>

